# Solution(Back Traking)

```java
class Solution {

    static LinkedList<TreeNode> l=new LinkedList<>();
    static LinkedList<TreeNode> l1,l2;
    static TreeNode lowestCommonAncestor(TreeNode root, TreeNode p, TreeNode q) {
        l.add(root);
        backTracking(root,p,0);
        backTracking(root,q,1);
        int index=0;
        while(index< l1.size()
                &&index<l2.size()
                &&l1.get(index)==l2.get(index)){
            index++;
        }
        Stack<TreeNode>s=new Stack<>();
        s.push(root);
        while(!s.isEmpty()){
            TreeNode node=s.pop();
            if(node==l1.get(index-1)){
                return node;
            }
            if(node.right!=null){
                s.push(node.right);
            }
            if(node.left!=null){
                s.push(node.left);
            }
        }
        return root;
    }
    static void backTracking(TreeNode root, TreeNode node,int num){
        if(root==node){
            if(num==0){
                l1= (LinkedList) l.clone();
            }else{
                l2= (LinkedList) l.clone();
            }
            return;
        }
        if(root.left!=null){
            l.add(root.left);
            backTracking(root.left,node,num);
            l.removeLast();
        }
        if(root.right!=null){
            l.add(root.right);
            backTracking(root.right,node,num);
            l.removeLast();
        }
    }
}
```

- time:*O(n)*

- space:*O(n)*


# Solution(Recursion)

```java
class Solution {
    public TreeNode lowestCommonAncestor(TreeNode root, TreeNode p, TreeNode q) {
        if (root == null || root == p || root == q){
			return root;
        }            
        TreeNode left = lowestCommonAncestor(root.left, p, q);
        TreeNode right = lowestCommonAncestor(root.right, p, q);
        if (left != null && right != null){
        	return root;
        }else{
			return left != null ? left : right;
        }        

    }
}
```

